Class TelnetTerminal

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.lanterna.terminal.AbstractTerminal
      • com.googlecode.lanterna.terminal.ansi.StreamBasedTerminal
        • com.googlecode.lanterna.terminal.ansi.ANSITerminal
          • com.googlecode.lanterna.terminal.ansi.TelnetTerminal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InputProvider, ExtendedTerminal, Terminal

    public class TelnetTerminal
extends ANSITerminal
    This class is used by the TelnetTerminalServer class when a client has connected in; this class will be the interaction point for that client. All operations are sent to the client over the network socket and some of the meta-operations (like echo mode) are communicated using Telnet negotiation language.

    A good resource on telnet communication is http://www.tcpipguide.com/free/t_TelnetProtocol.htm Also here: http://support.microsoft.com/kb/231866

    Author:
    martin
